data.content:
These are three well-known C# 13 breaking changes. Here's what breaks and the fixes:

**1. Buffer.cs** — `[InlineArray]` is no longer allowed on `record struct` (records synthesize methods that violate inline array rules).

```csharp
[System.Runtime.CompilerServices.InlineArray(10)]
struct Buffer            // change: record struct → struct
{
    private int _element0;
}
```

**2. Generator.cs** — C# 13 forbids `stackalloc` in local functions inside iterator methods. Extract it to a standalone method:

```csharp
unsafe class DataGenerator
{
    IEnumerable<int> Generate()
    {
        yield return 1;
        Process();
    }

    // moved out of the iterator
    static void Process()
    {
        int* p = stackalloc int[10];
        // ... work with pointer
    }
}
```

**3. Resolver.cs** — C# 13's `params Span<T>` support changes overload resolution; `[]` is now ambiguous between `ReadOnlySpan<int>` and `Span<object>`. Disambiguate with an explicit cast:

```csharp
class Resolver
{
    static void Process(ReadOnlySpan<int> ros) {}
    static void Process(Span<object> s) {}

    static void Main()
    {
        Process((ReadOnlySpan<int>)[]);  // explicit target type
    }
}
```
